==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Teinoscope
<hw>Tei"no*scope</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ to
extend + <ets>-scope</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>An
instrument formed by combining prisms so as to correct the chromatic
aberration of the light while linear dimensions of objects seen through
the prisms are increased or diminished; -- called also <altname>prism
telescope</altname>.</def> <rj><au>Sir D. Brewster.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Teint</ent>⟦br⟧
